            "question_text": "A and B start running simultaneously towards each other from the two ends of a track XY and the ratio of their speeds is 3 : 4. Every time they meet, they interchange their speeds and also reverse their directions. At how many distinct points on the track do they meet each other, if they run continuously between 2 ends of the tracks? (Track XY is shown below) <ul class='list-group'> <li class='list-group-item'><B><a href='#quesSol1617357' data-toggle='collapse' aria-expanded='true'> Answer key/Solution</a></B></li> </ul>",
            "options": [],
